The paper deals with adversarial machine learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and computer security. The paper proposes a method for evaluating the robustness of deep neural networks and analyzes the current state-of-the-art models and defenses. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
